edu.stanford.smi.protegex.owl.ui.dialogs
Interface SelectionDialogFactory

All Known Implementing Classes:
AbstractSelectionDialogFactory, DefaultSelectionDialogFactory
public interface SelectionDialogFactory

An interface for user interface dialogs to select resources from a list or tree.

An instance of this can be accessed from ProtegeUI.getSelectionDialogFactory().

All methods take a Component as first argument which can be left null: if no pointer to an existing component is available then the system will use the ProjectView registered for the OWLModel. However, it is generally recommended to use a non-null parent.

Author:
Holger Knublauch
